   "source": [
    "Real-Life AI Applications and Their ML Working\n",
    "1)Google Search\n",
    " Uses ML algorithms to rank search results based on relevance, user behavior, and past searches.\n",
    "\n",
    "2)YouTube Recommendations\n",
    " Machine learning analyzes watch history, likes, and viewing patterns to suggest personalized videos.\n",
    "\n",
    "3)Smartphone Face Unlock\n",
    " ML models learn facial features and patterns to accurately identify and authenticate the user.\n",
    "\n",
    "4)Google Maps\n",
    " Uses ML to predict traffic conditions and suggest optimal routes based on real-time and historical data.\n",
    "\n",
    "5)Voice Assistants (Google Assistant / Alexa)\n",
    " ML processes speech patterns to understand voice commands and provide accurate responses.\n",
    "\n",
    "6)Email Spam Filters\n",
    " Machine learning classifies emails as spam or safe by learning from previously marked messages.\n",
    "\n",
    "7)Netflix Recommendations\n",
    " ML algorithms analyze viewing history and preferences to suggest movies and TV shows.\n",
    "\n",
    "8)Autocorrect and Predictive Text\n",
    " Uses ML to predict words and correct spelling based on typing patterns and language models.\n",
    "\n",
    "9)Online Shopping Suggestions (Amazon / Flipkart)\n",
    " ML analyzes browsing and purchase history to recommend relevant products.\n",
    "\n",
    "10)Social Media Feeds (Instagram / Facebook)\n",
    " Machine learning decides which posts appear first by analyzing likes, comments, and interaction patterns."
   ]
